        "pf_e508e8df_value": "“This is the coldest unit we have ever purchased while living in a mobile home, we have two other units in the bedrooms and they are 8,000btu yet we have to use blackout curtains to shade the sun to still keep the trailer cool.This unit is 12,000btu and AMAZING! set it up and within 10 minutes it was ice cold at 1 pm, the hottest of the day while 84 outside! It maintained 70-71 with no issues until we literally had to turn it back we got so cold! . ”",
        "pf_203b0629_value": "“We put it in our converted garage and it cools it down very well. It’s about a 300 square foot room. I put a fan in the doorway during the summer when it’s super hot and it helps cool off the main room and kitchen as well. We just wanted to take some pressure off the main unit and it works better than we expected. We self installed it. I didn’t know anything about AC stuff but you can definitely figure it out on YouTube. . ”",
        "pf_ef193103_value": "<strong><a href=\"https://dellahome.com/blogs/della-blog/mini-split-thermostat-settings\" target=\"_self\"></a><a href=\"https://dellahome.com/blogs/della-blog/mini-split-thermostat-settings\" target=\"_blank\">Best Mini Split Thermostat Settings for Efficiency and Comfort</a><br><sub><span style=\"color: rgb(155, 155, 155);\">DELLA</span><span style=\"color: rgb(155, 155, 155);\"></span></sub><br></strong>",
        "pf_bcfd4c22_value": "“I purchased the 12,000 BTU 115V so I could install it in my garage without an electrician, it heats and cools very quickly. I bought 12gauge wire to handle 20amp per the manual and wired that into a 20amp outlet plug instead of working directly to the breaker box. since garages in my residential area have standard 20amp breaker it was easy to use 12gauge 20amp wire and a 20amp outlet. ”",
        "pf_f8ba0149_value": "So far so good! First I installed the condenser unit on the wall but the vibration made a little humming noise. Then I installed a platform with vibration stands and the noise totally went away. I currently have it set up on a daily schedule and it keeps my sunroom at 73 degrees in 20 degree weather. Now I can watch sports and movies in the sunroom comfortably.",
